    %p{:style => "text-align: right;"}
      %strong Lounasaika.net API V1 BETA
      %br/
      (updated 2012-12-05)
      %p
        %h1 Audience
        %p This document is intended for website and mobile developers who want to use student restaurant menu data provided by Lounasaika.net API. It provides an introduction to using this API. Any feedback will be greatly appreciated.
        %p
          Please note that you are strongly encouraged to register your app by sending an email to api@lounasaika.net.
        %h1 Availability
        %p
          The service is hosted by
          %a{:href => "http://pages.github.com/"} Github Pages
          which ensures excellent availability.
        %h1 Requests
        %p
          Lounasaika.net API supports one request which provides all restaurant menus for current week:
        %p
          %em http://www.lounasaika.net/api/v1/menus.json
        %p The JSON returned by this request is shown below. Note that actual JSON may contain less whitespace. You should not make assumptions about the amount or format of whitespace between requests.
        %p The example contains two restaurants, Teekkariravintolat and TUAS-talo, which are both located on the same campus, Otaniemi. Opening times are fixed form and nicely parsable. URL's for available languages are listed under 'url' element. Under 'meals' element you can find menus in all available languages (currently Finnish and English).
